sect1:
iptables-&iptables-version;


The next part of this chapter deals with firewalling.  The
principle firewalling tool for Linux, as of the 2.4 kernel series, is
iptables.  It replaces
ipchains from the 2.2 series and
ipfwadm from the
2.0 series. You will need to install iptables if 
you intend on using any form of firewalling.

